## 6. Screen 3 — The Bridge

### 6.1 Purpose

After the 12-month section closes, the user reaches the bridge — a single synthesized block that distills the entire synthesis into a current-quarter strategic posture. This is the transition point between synthesis and action.

### 6.2 Layout

Visually distinct from the accordion sections above. Full-width card or panel — styled to signal a shift in mode. This is no longer reflection; this is the beginning of planning.

**Contents:**

Label (small caps or muted label style): `YOUR QUARTER FOCUS`

A single paragraph — two to four sentences — that expresses the current-quarter strategic posture in plain language. This is not a list of capabilities. It is a statement of intent. Example:

*"For this quarter, the most structurally important work centers on financial visibility and role clarity across your delivery team. These aren't the only things that matter — but they're the ones where progress now creates the most leverage for everything that follows. Your quarter should be organized around these foundations."*

The specific theme areas referenced in this paragraph are drawn from the 12-month synthesis and expressed at the capability area or dimension level — not as specific checkpoints.

**CTA Button:**

Primary button, prominent, centered:

`Build My Quarter Map →`

Routes to: `/pro/planning/quarter-map`

Below the button, a secondary line:
`You'll select your 9 focus capability areas using the 3P Framework — Prioritize, Plant, and Progressively Iterate.`

This prepares the user for what they are about to do without requiring them to read separate instructions on the next screen.

