## 7. Navigation & State Management

- The user can return to the declaration screen at any time via a secondary back link at the top of the synthesis screen: `← Back to Horizon Declaration`
- Returning to the declaration screen does not clear the synthesis — it preserves it unless the user explicitly confirms a change and re-triggers generation
- If the user updates their Clarity Compass and returns to the roadmap, the synthesis is marked stale and the confirm button reflects this: `Vision Updated — Regenerate Synthesis`
- Synthesis results are stored in Supabase against the user record and associated with the planning session quarter
- Quarter is determined by the current calendar quarter at the time of synthesis generation

